==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mephitis
<hw>Me*phi"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mephitis</ets> : cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧phitis</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Noxious, pestilential, or foul exhalations from
decomposing substances, filth, or other source.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of mammals, including the
skunks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mephitism</ent>⟦br⟧
